Here are the commands to export your Pieces data:

  # Create a timestamped backup of all your Pieces data
  cp -R ~/Library/com.pieces.os/production ~/Desktop/pieces-backup-$(date
  +%Y%m%d)

  Or if you want a compressed archive:

  # Create a compressed zip archive
  zip -r ~/Desktop/pieces-backup-$(date +%Y%m%d).zip
  ~/Library/com.pieces.os/production

  To extract and read individual saved pieces:

  # List all your saved pieces
  ls ~/Library/com.pieces.os/production/Pieces/Formats/

  # Decompress a specific piece to view its contents
  gunzip -c ~/Library/com.pieces.os/production/Pieces/Formats/<uuid>.piece

  To query the database directly:

  # Open the SQLite database
  sqlite3
  ~/Library/com.pieces.os/production/Pieces/couchbase.cblite2/db.sqlite3

  # Once inside, list tables with:
  .tables

  # Export a table to CSV:
  .mode csv
  .output ~/Desktop/pieces-tags.csv
  SELECT * FROM "kv_.tags";
  .quit